wifi: mt76: mt7925: add MT6639 MLO (Multi-Link Operation) support

Enable WiFi 7 Multi-Link Operation on MT6639/MT7927 combo chips.
MT6639 has two radios (band0=2.4GHz, band1=5GHz/6GHz shared), requiring
explicit band_idx assignment unlike MT7925 which uses 0xff (auto-select).

Key changes:
- Force MT792x_CHIP_CAP_MLO_EN: firmware doesn't report MLO in NIC_CAP
- Assign concrete band_idx (0=2.4G, 1=5/6G) throughout the driver:
  mac_link_bss_add, assign_vif_chanctx, ROC grant/set/abort, BSS basic TLV
- Per-link omac_idx for STR dual-link (MT7925 eMLSR uses 0 for all)
- Fix ROC for all cross-band combinations, not just 2.4G primary
- Fix broadcast/multicast RX in MLO mode (def_wcid for BSS self-STA)
- Clear 6GHz NO_IR for indoor active scanning (LPI mode)
- Correct BSS_MLD TLV field ordering based on Windows driver RE

The band_idx fix also resolves the 4WAY_HANDSHAKE_TIMEOUT on 5/6 GHz
that was independently discovered by marcin-fm.

All changes guarded by is_mt6639() - no impact on MT7925 behavior.

Tested: 5GHz+2.4GHz MLO (STR), 6GHz+2.4GHz MLO, single-link all bands.

Co-developed-by: marcin-fm <marcin-fm@users.noreply.github.com>
Signed-off-by: marcin-fm <marcin-fm@users.noreply.github.com>
Signed-off-by: 张旭涵 <Loong.0x00@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
